Four more people are in a critical condition and five bodies have yet to be identified. This follows the death of over 20 young people at an East London tavern. Premier Oscar Mabuyane says the provincial government is assisting families to identify their loved ones. #eNCA #DStv403 EAST LONDON - Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane says the provincial government is assisting families to identify loved ones following the tragedy at Enyobeni Tavern. Over 20 people died at the tavern in Scenery Park in the Eastern Cape. READ: Liquor Trader Council: EC tavern owner to blame The youngest of the victims is believed to be 13 years old. Meanwhile, four more people are in critical condition and five bodies have yet to be identified.